cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.CR, cs.MM, cs.HC

The paper deals with iris recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV) and image processing (cs.IR). It also involves biometrics (cs.CR) and medical imaging (cs.MM) as it deals with post-mortem changes to the iris and their impact on biometric identification. Additionally, the paper discusses the usability of iris recognition for identification purposes, which falls under human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
